%20exposed%20following%20Hamas's%20attack%20on%20Israel%20on%20October%207%2C%202023.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20on%20October%2018%2C%20Netanyahu's%20hold%20on%20power%20seemed%20stronger%20than%20it%20had%20been%20after%20announcing%20the%20death%20of%20Hamas%20leader%20Yahya%20Sinwar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20killing%20of%20Sinwar%2C%20who%20orchestrated%20October%207%20attacks%2C%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20vindication%20for%20Prime%20Minister%20Netanyahu%2C%20Israel's%20longest-serving%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBackground%20and%20political%20career%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20on%20October%2021%2C%201949%2C%20in%20Tel%20Aviv%2C%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu's%20mother%2C%20Tzila%20Segal%2C%20was%20an%20Israeli-born%20Jew%2C%20while%20his%20father%2C%20Benzion%20Netanyahu%2C%20was%20from%20Poland%20who%20changed%20his%20name%20from%20Benzion%20Mileikowsky%20upon%20settling%20in%20Jerusalem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBenjamin%20Netanyahu%20was%20raised%20in%20Jerusalem%20and%20attended%20high%20school%20in%20the%20US.%20His%20father%20was%20a%20historian.%20In%201963%2C%20the%20family%20moved%20to%20Philadelphia%2C%20US%2C%20where%20he%20spent%20his%20formative%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2018%2C%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20returned%20to%20Israel%20and%20served%20five%20years%20in%20the%20Israel%20Defense%20Forces%20(IDF)%20as%20a%20captain%20in%20the%20elite%20Sayeret%20Matkal%20commando%20unit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20his%20military%20service%2C%20Netanyahu%20pursued%20higher%20education%20at%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20(MIT)%2C%20earning%20an%20MBA%20in%201976.%20His%20studies%20were%20briefly%20interrupted%20by%20the%20Yom%20Kippur%20War%20in%201973%2C%20where%20he%20served%20as%20a%20soldier.%20The%20loss%20of%20his%20brother%20Jonathan%20during%20the%20Entebbe%20raid%20in%201976%20spurred%20him%20to%20establish%20the%20Jonathan%20Institute%2C%20dedicated%20to%20addressing%20terrorism-related%20issues%20through%20international%20conferences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFluent%20in%20English%20with%20a%20notable%20American%20accent%2C%20he%20quickly%20became%20a%20prominent%20voice%20for%20Israel%2C%20frequently%20appearing%20on%20US%20television%20as%20a%20strong%20advocate%20for%20his%20country.%20In%201982%2C%20he%20became%20Israel's%20deputy%20chief%20of%20mission%20in%20Washington.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20he%20was%20appointed%20Israel's%20permanent%20representative%20to%20the%20United%20Nations%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBenjamin%20Netanyahu's%20political%20career%20truly%20began%20in%201988%20when%20he%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20Knesset%20(Israel's%20parliament)%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Likud%20party.%20He%20swiftly%20rose%20through%20the%20ranks%2C%20serving%20as%20deputy%20foreign%20minister%20from%201988%20to%201991%20and%20later%20as%20deputy%20minister.%20In%201993%2C%20he%20became%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20Likud%20party%2C%20gaining%20prominence%20for%20his%20staunch%20opposition%20to%20the%20Israel-PLO%20peace%20accords%20and%20the%20subsequent%20Israeli%20withdrawals%20from%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENetanyahu's%20first%20term%20as%20PM%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2047%2C%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20became%20Israel's%20youngest%20prime%20minister%20after%20the%201996%20elections.%20His%20tenure%20began%20amid%20unrest%2C%20with%20strained%20relations%20with%20Syria%20and%20backlash%20from%20his%20decision%20to%20open%20a%20tunnel%20near%20the%20Al-Aqsa%20Mosque%2C%20sparking%20violent%20clashes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20his%20staunch%20opposition%20to%20the%201993%20Oslo%20peace%20accords%2C%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20made%20notable%20concessions%20during%20his%20first%20term%20as%20PM.%20He%20signed%20an%20agreement%20transferring%2080%25%20of%20Hebron%20to%20Palestinian%20Authority%20control%20and%20approved%20further%20withdrawals%20from%20the%20occupied%20West%20Bank%2C%20moves%20that%20drew%20sharp%20criticism%20from%20his%20right-wing%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201999%2C%20after%20calling%20early%20elections%2017%20months%20ahead%20of%20schedule%2C%20Netanyahu%20was%20defeated%20by%20Labour%20leader%20Ehud%20Barak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20this%20loss%2C%20Netanyahu%20remained%20a%20prominent%20figure%20in%20Likud%20but%20lost%20the%20party%20leadership%20to%20Ariel%20Sharon.%20He%20later%20served%20as%20foreign%20minister%20and%20finance%20minister%20in%20Sharon's%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReturn%20to%20power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20February%202009%20elections%2C%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu's%20Likud%20party%20secured%2027%20seats%20in%20the%20Knesset%2C%20narrowly%20trailing%20Kadima's%2028.%20Netanyahu%20formed%20a%20coalition%20government%20with%20Yisrael%20Beiteinu%2C%20Shas%20and%20smaller%20parties%2C%20officially%20assuming%20office%20on%20March%2031%2C%202009.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20term%2C%20Netanyahu%20offered%20conditional%20support%20for%20a%20Palestinian%20state%2C%20but%20insisted%20it%20be%20demilitarised%20and%20recognise%20Israel%20as%20a%20Jewish%20state%20-%20conditions%20rejected%20by%20Palestinian%20leaders.%20Peace%20talks%20stalled%20in%202010%20after%20Israel%20ended%20a%20moratorium%20on%20West%20Bank%20settlements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENetanyahu's%20foreign%20policy%20was%20defined%20by%20his%20hardline%20stance%20on%20Iran%2C%20consistently%20advocating%20for%20international%20action%20against%20its%20nuclear%20programme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDomestically%2C%20rising%20economic%20discontent%20triggered%20mass%20protests%20in%202011%2C%20with%20citizens%20demanding%20better%20public%20services.%20His%20coalition%20also%20struggled%20with%20tensions%20over%20military%20draft%20exemptions%20for%20ultra-Orthodox%20Jews%2C%20leading%20to%20early%20elections%20in%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20returning%20to%20power%20post%20the%20elections%20with%20a%20more%20centrist%20coalition%2C%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20led%20a%20military%20operation%20in%20Gaza%20in%202014%20following%20rocket%20attacks.%20Despite%20international%20criticism%20over%20civilian%20casualties%2C%20he%20claimed%20the%20operation%20weakened%20militant%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20late%202014%2C%20internal%20strife%20within%20his%20coalition%20over%20budget%20and%20legislation%20led%20to%20the%20dismissal%20of%20key%20cabinet%20members%20and%20elections%20in%202015.%20Relations%20with%20then%20US%20President%20Barack%20Obama%20became%20increasingly%20strained%2C%20particularly%20over%20Iran%2C%20culminating%20in%20Netanyahu's%20controversial%20address%20to%20the%20US%20Congress%20in%20early%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20predictions%20of%20a%20tight%20race%20in%20the%20March%202015%20elections%2C%20Netanyahu's%20Likud%20party%20emerged%20victorious.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECorruption%20allegations%20and%20coalition%20crises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBenjamin%20Netanyahu%20faced%20charges%20of%20fraud%2C%20breach%20of%20trust%20and%20corruption%20stemming%20from%20long-running%20investigations.%20Indicted%20in%202019%2C%20he%20was%20accused%20of%20accepting%20lavish%20gifts%20from%20millionaire%20associates%20and%20seeking%20regulatory%20favours%20for%20media%20moguls%20in%20exchange%20for%20positive%20coverage.%20Netanyahu%20denied%20any%20wrongdoing%20and%20refused%20to%20resign%20following%20his%20indictment%2C%20branding%20the%20investigations%20a%20politically%20motivated%20witch-hunt%20orchestrated%20by%20law%20enforcement%2C%20the%20media%20and%20the%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20corruption%20allegations%20became%20a%20rallying%20point%20for%20opposition%20parties%2C%20uniting%20politicians%20from%20across%20Israel's%20political%20spectrum.%20This%20growing%20opposition%20ultimately%20led%20to%20his%20ouster%20after%20the%20March%202021%20elections%2C%20ending%20Netanyahu's%20another%20term%20as%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2022%20electoral%20comeback%20and%20controversy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20early%202022%2C%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu's%20corruption%20trial%20faced%20setbacks%20after%20reports%20surfaced%20that%20police%20had%20used%20Pegasus%20spyware%20to%20hack%20the%20phones%20of%20key%20witnesses.%20Netanyahu's%20defence%20further%20questioned%20the%20allegations%2C%20citing%20an%20incorrect%20meeting%20date%20in%20the%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20opposition%20leader%2C%20Netanyahu%20aggressively%20targeted%20the%20ruling%20coalition.%20The%20November%202022%20elections%20saw%20a%20record%20voter%20turnout%2C%20with%20Netanyahu%20returning%20to%20power%20through%20a%20controversial%20coalition%20that%20included%20far-right%20ministers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIsrael-Hamas%20war%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%207%2C%202023%2C%20Hamas%20launched%20a%20massive%20attack%20on%20Israel%20by%20land%2C%20sea%2C%20and%20air.%20In%20response%2C%20Israel%20launched%20airstrikes%20on%20Gaza.%20A%20ground%20invasion%20soon%20followed%2C%20intensifying%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBenjamin%20Netanyahu%20faced%20heavy%20criticism%20for%20his%20handling%20of%20the%20crisis%2C%20blamed%20for%20both%20the%20unpreparedness%20leading%20up%20to%20October%207%20and%20the%20management%20of%20hostages%20and%20displaced%20civilians.%20Polls%20showed%20declining%20support%20for%20Netanyahu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternationally%2C%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20saw%20a%20shift%20from%20initial%20sympathy%20to%20isolation%20due%20to%20deteriorating%20conditions%20in%20Gaza.%20By%20March%202024%2C%20he%20faced%20a%20rift%20with%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20over%20a%20planned%20offensive%20in%20Rafah%2C%20an%20area%20with%20a%20large%20concentration%20of%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDomestic%20unrest%20grew%20as%20protests%20intensified%20in%20Tel%20Aviv%20by%20late%20May.%20On%20May%2020%2C%202024%2C%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20announced%20plans%20to%20seek%20arrest%20warrants%20for%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%2C%20Defence%20Minister%20Yoav%20Gallant%20and%20Hamas%20leaders%20for%20alleged%20war%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20decision%20drew%20condemnation%2C%20though%20Netanyahu's%20public%20support%20rose%20slightly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202024%2C%20Netanyahu%20insisted%20that%20any%20ceasefire%20must%20allow%20Israel%20to%20retain%20control%20over%20the%20Philadelphi%20Corridor%20between%20Gaza%20and%20Egypt%2C%20viewing%20it%20as%20critical%20to%20cutting%20off%20Hamas's%20supplies.%20This%20became%20a%20sticking%20point%20in%20negotiations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20August%2C%20the%20discovery%20of%20the%20bodies%20of%20six%20hostages%20escalated%20public%20anger%2C%20triggering%20massive%20protests.%20The%20protesters%20demanded%20the%20Netanyahu%20government%20to%20prioritise%20the%20release%20of%20remaining%20hostages.%20Despite%20growing%20pressure%2C%20Netanyahu%20maintained%20his%20stance%20on%20controlling%20the%20Philadelphi%20Corridor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20is%20also%20fighting%20a%20war%20with%20Hamas%20ally%20Hezbollah%20in%20Lebanon.%20The%20two%20sides%20had%20exchanged%20rocket%20fire%20since%20the%20October%207%20attack.%20The%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20government%20decided%20to%20send%20ground%20troops%20to%20Lebanon%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20remains%20very%20tense%20with%20the%20world%20eagerly%20watching%20Benjamin%20Neyanyahu's%20next%20step.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20killing%20of%20Hamas%20leader%20Yahya%20Sinwar%2C%20the%20mastermind%20of%20the%20October%207%20attacks%2C%20has%20significantly%20boosted%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu's%20image%20within%20Israel%20but%20it%20may%20escalate%20tension%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729343520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F20