ncies%20to%20quit%20their%20jobs.%C2%A0Momuri%2C%20a%20Tokyo-based%20agency%2C%20has%20reported%20a%20major%20spike%20in%20demand%20ever%20since%20it%20began%20offering%20proxy%20resignation%20services%20more%20than%20two%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EShinji%20Tanimoto%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Albatross%2C%20the%20firm%20that%20runs%20Momuri%2C%20told%20The%20Guardian%20that%20they%20submit%20resignations%20on%20people's%20behalf%20as%20they%20are%20unable%20to%20do%20so%20for%20whatever%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20Japanese%2C%20Momuri%20means%20%26quot%3Benough%20already%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20it's%20just%20natural%20reluctance%2C%20but%20some%20might%20have%20experienced%20harassment%20or%20even%20violence%20from%20their%20employers.%20They%20are%20at%20their%20wits'%20end%20when%20they%20come%20to%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20official%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAt%20present%2C%20Momuri%20is%20among%20the%20estimated%20100%20companies%20that%20offer%20similar%20services%20across%20Japan.%20It%20has%20received%20a%20total%20of%20350%2C000%20online%20consultations%20and%20went%20on%20to%20complete%2020%2C000%20resignations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20it%20work%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFor%20this%20service%2C%20people%20usually%20get%20in%20touch%20with%20these%20agencies%20via%20popular%20messaging%20apps.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20Momuri%2C%20clients%20have%20to%20first%20complete%20a%20questionnaire%20and%20then%20sign%20a%20contract%2C%20besides%20paying%20the%20fee%20of%20%C2%A522%2C000%20(roughly%20%E2%82%B912%2C344)%20for%20full-time%20workers%20and%20%C2%A512%2C300%20(around%20%E2%82%B96%2C900)%20for%20part-time%20employees%20as%20well%20as%20those%20working%20on%20fixed-term%20contracts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOn%20behalf%20of%20the%20client%2C%20one%20of%20Momuri's%20staff%20calls%20the%20employer.%20The%20entire%20process%2C%20starting%20with%20the%20initial%20consultation%20to%20resignation%2C%20usually%20takes%2020-30%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20are%20people%20leaving%20jobs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESurprisingly%2C%2060%25%20of%20the%20Momuri%20users%20are%20those%20people%2C%20who%20are%20in%20their%2020s.%20As%20per%20Japan's%20labour%20ministry%2C%20over%2030%25%20of%20the%20recent%20graduates%20in%20the%20country%20are%20leaving%20their%20jobs%20within%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIf%20experts%20are%20to%20be%20believed%20then%20this%20growing%20trend%20is%20due%20to%20a%20generational%20shift%20in%20people's%20attitude%20towards%20work%20that%20has%20been%20accelerated%20by%20the%20disruption%20to%20jobs%20as%20well%20as%20the%20lifestyles%20caused%20by%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ELabour%20shortage%20in%20Japan%20--%20a%20symptom%20of%20its%20low%20birthrate%20--%20has%20further%20made%20employers%20more%20determined%20towards%20retaining%20the%20staff%20members%2C%20even%20when%20it%20requires%20intimidating%20them%20into%20staying%20back.%20Also%2C%20there%20have%20been%20instances%20when%20they%20have%20allegedly%20forced%20workers%20to%20hunt%20for%20their%20own%20replacements%20before%20accepting%20their%20resignations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMynavi%2C%20an%20employment%20information%20provider%20in%20Japan%2C%20said%20that%20one%20in%20six%20workers%20in%20the%20country%20took%20help%20from%20resignation%20agencies%20to%20switch%20to%20another%20company%20in%20the%2012%20months%20period%2C%20till%20June%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1729336380000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2Fubndul7o_job-resignation-generic_625x300_16_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originI